Third-party components (selected; full lockfile SBOM via `script/generate_sbom.py`)

Governed Tier-0 PDF parsing (document worker):
  - pypdf — BSD-3-Clause
  - pdfminer.six — MIT
  - charset-normalizer, cryptography, cffi, pycparser — see their upstream licenses
    (captured in docs/dependency-governance/pdf-parser-approval.md)

Optional / opt-in:
  - onnxruntime — MIT (extra: rsi-atlas-ingestion[onnx])
  - sentence-transformers all-MiniLM-L6-v2 ONNX weights — Apache-2.0
    (install via script/install_embedding_model.py --download; not bundled by default)
  - duckdb — MIT (extra: rsi-atlas-collectors[duckdb]; gated by RSI_ATLAS_ENABLE_DUCKDB=1)

Core runtime (representative):
  - pydantic, packaging, psycopg, httpx — see PyPI / uv.lock
  - PostgreSQL 17 + pgvector — PostgreSQL License / their upstream terms
  - Swift / SwiftUI / Apple SDKs — Apple license terms (macOS build only)

Docling remains blocked and is not a runtime dependency.
A CycloneDX SBOM can be generated from the pinned lockfile without Apple signing secrets.
